<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920120-0047</DOCNO><DOCID>920120-0047.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- TCBY Enterprises Inc.:   Frozen-Yogurt Retailer Has   $1.4 Million Quarterly Loss</HL><DATE>01/20/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   TBY</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>ENTERTAINMENT AND LEISURE (ENT)EARNINGS (ERN)RESTAURANTS, FAST-FOOD, CATERING (RES)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>ARKANSAS (AR)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   TCBY Enterprises Inc. said it had a loss of $1.4 million,or five cents a share, for the fourth quarter, ended Nov. 30,compared with a profit of $400,000, or two cents a share, inthe year-earlier period.   The frozen-yogurt store franchiser, which has beenstruggling with a glut of outlets, said in Little Rock, Ark.,that revenue fell 7.3% in the period, to $25.1 million from$27.1 million the previous year. Sales at stores open morethan a year fell 5%.</LP><TEXT>   The company said its selling and administrative expenserose by $1 million, or 8%, during the quarter, largelybecause of an increase in company-operated stores.   For the year, TCBY had net income of $8 million, or 31cents a share, a drop of almost 60% from $20 million, or 75cents a share, in fiscal 1990. It said revenue fell almost15%, to $128.9 million from $151.3 million, largely becausestore additions slowed, reducing its revenue from initialfranchise fees and equipment sales.</TEXT></DOC>